text.tspan: Abide in me, Lord, deep within my heart
Experience of Christ — Abiding in Him
Your Spirit with my spirit is the key—
A mutual dwelling place for You and me!
By this organic union that we share
We have become by grace one loving pair.
By faith I have been joined to You, dear Lord,
Now our two spirits are in one accord!
Thus joined and mingled, I abide in You,
In thought, intention, and in all I do.
“Abide in Me and I’ll abide in you,”
Both a commandment and a promise true!
We may much fruit unto the Father bear
As we abide in Him whose life we share.
